   <head>The ANSWER.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">THE noble art to Cadmus owes its rise,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Of painting words, and speaking to the eyes;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">He first in wond'rous magic fetters bound</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The airy voice, and stop'd the flying sound:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The various figures by his pencil wrought,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Gave colour, form, and body to the thought.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
